Iran strongly warns Zionists against invading Al Aqsa Mosque

TEHRAN, Aug. 27 (MNA) – Iran has warned Zionists against any encroachment on the sacred sanctity of the Al-Aqsa Mosque and the new adventurism of the Zionists in crossing the red lines of the Islamic Ummah.

By: Seyed Saeed Reza Razavi

Introduction ceremony of Iran's new foreign minister

TEHRAN, Aug. 27 (MNA) – A ceremony for the introduction of the new foreign minister of Iran Abbas Araghchi was held on Tuesday with the participation of new Iranian President Masoud Pezeshkian.

By: Mohsen Ranginkaman

Ceremony of National Defense Industry Day in Tehran

TEHRAN, Aug. 27 (MNA) – The commemoration ceremony of the National Defense Industry Day was held in Tehran on Tue. with the participation of Deputy Minister of Defense Brigadier General Hojjaollah Qoreyshi and foreign military attaches in Iran.

Stoltenberg:

NATO-Ukraine Council to meet on August 28 at Kyiv’s request

TEHRAN, Aug. 27 (MNA) – Jens Stoltenberg said that on August 28 he would convene a meeting of the NATO-Ukraine council at the request of Kiev.

At least 17 dead, 11 missing after heavy rainfall in Gujarat

TEHRAN, Aug. 27 (MNA) – At least 17 people have been killed and 11 others are missing in rain-related incidents in the western Indian state of Gujarat, officials said on Tuesday.

Iran blasts ex-UN rapporteur presence alongside terror chiefs

TEHRAN, Aug. 27 (MNA) – A member of Iran’s Guardian Council, Abbas Ali Kadkhodaei said that the presence of the former UN special rapporteur on the situation of human rights in Iran Javaid Rehman alongside terror cults speaks volumes.

Yi hopes talks with Sullivan can 'remove obstacles' to ties

Kyiv test-fires 1st home-grown ballistic missile: Zelensky

TEHRAN, Aug. 27 (MNA) – Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky said on Tuesday that Kiev military has recently carried out the first successful test of a domestically produced ballistic missile.

Hezbollah destroys Israeli spy equipment in Dovev Barracks

TEHRAN, Aug. 27 (MNA) – Lebanon's Hezbollah announced that it has targeted the spying equipment of the Israeli forces in the north of occupied Palestine.

Iran's response to Zionist regime’s crime ‘definite’: Envoy

TEHRAN, Aug. 27 (MNA) – Iranian ambassador to Beirut in a message on Tuesday emphasized that Iran’s response to the Israeli assassination of ex-Hamas Chief Ismail Haniyeh in Tehran is ‘definite’ and the timing is determined by Iran’s military forces.

Lavrov:

Ukraine demand to West about Storm Shadow missile blackmail

TEHRAN, Aug. 27 (MNA) – Russian Foreign Minister Sergey Lavrov in a press conference with his Yemeni counterpart, stated that Ukraine's demands to the West to allow the use of Storm Shadow missiles on Moscow and St. Petersburg are blackmail.

Biden holds talk with India’s Modi after Ukraine visit

TEHRAN, Aug. 27 (MNA) – US President Joe Biden discussed various issues, including the dimensions of his visit to Ukraine in a phone call with Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi.

US forces move weapons, ammunitions to their base in Syria

TEHRAN, Aug. 27 (MNA) – The US forces have sent a new weapons convoy to one of their bases in eastern Syria.

By: Ali Haddadi Asl

Introduction, farewell ceremony of Iran's health minister

TEHRAN, Aug. 27 (MNA) – A ceremony for the introduction of new health minister and farewell of the previous health minister was held at Ministry of Health compound on Tuesday with the participation of new Iranian President Masoud Pezeshkian.

Pezeshkian congratulates students on astronomy olympiad win

TEHRAN, Aug. 27 (MNA) – Masoud Pezeshkian, the new Iranian president, has offered congratulations to Iranian students for winning gold medals in International Olympiad on Astronomy and Astrophysics (IOAA).

Grossi says there is risk of nuclear incident in Kursk plant

TEHRAN, Aug. 27 (MNA) – The UN nuclear agency chief Rafael Grossi said after visiting Russia's Kursk nuclear power plant on Tuesday that there was a risk of a "nuclear incident" and the situation was serious.

Zuckerberg says Biden ‘pressured’ Facebook to censure content

TEHRAN, Aug. 27 (MNA) – The Meta boss, Mark Zuckerberg, has said he regrets bowing to what he claims was pressure from the US government to censor posts about Covid on Facebook and Instagram during the pandemic.

Hazrat Abbas Shrine Museum

TEHRAN, Aug. 27 (MNA) – Holy Shrine Of Abu Fadhl Al-Abbas is located near the Imam Husayn Mosque in Karbala, Iraq. Inside the shrine compound, their is one of the prominent museums in Iraq which receives many visitors during Arbaeen procession.

VIDEO: Moment when Zionists bombarded house in Gaza

TEHRAN, Aug. 27 (MNA) – Footage shows the moment when the Zionists bombarded a house in the Gaza Strip.

Iran’s trade with 15 neighboring states up 16% in 5 months

TEHRAN, Aug. 27 (MNA) – Iran’s non-oil trade with 15 neighboring states in the first five months of the current Iranian calendar year (started March 21, 2024) registered a 16% growth compared to the last year's corresponding period.
